    "Most often, the interesting part of the image is around the peak, and you can get extra contrast by clipping the regions above and/or below the peak. In our histogram, it looks like theres not much useful information in the high end (not many white things in the image). Lets adjust the upper limit, so that we effectively zoom in on part of the histogram. We do this by setting the the `clim` for the plot:"
